   <abstract>Handwritten note sent to Mrs. Carroll B. McLean Fort Meyers, FLorida on November 7, 1959 for a postage of 3 cents.</abstract>
   <abstract>At entrance to the Great Smoky Mountains National Park. A modern hotel located in the heart of Gatlinburg. Ample parking space. Shaded grounds overlooking river. 100 air-conditioned, comfortable rooms with private bath. Hotel cars available for scenic tours. Temperature-controlled swimming pool. New air-conditioned dirning room overlooking patio and pool. Phone 373. J. T. Trotter, Mgr.</abstract>
